description.plain: Isaiah Firebrace (born 21 November 1999) is an Australian singer who won the eighth season of The X Factor Australia in 2016.

body.plain: Isaiah Firebrace (born 21 November 1999) is an Australian singer who won the eighth season of The X Factor Australia in 2016.

songs.full_title: It's Gotta Be You by Isaiah Firebrace
songs.title: It’s Gotta Be You

description.plain: Written originally by Anthony Egizii and David Musumeci, this song was sang by the farewell season winner from The X Factor Australia, Isaiah Firebrace. There is a lot of different explanation for this song however it mainly revolves around Isaiah and a girl that he has broken up with a few weeks ago so a fairly recent relationship. Explaining how he shouldn’t have let her go when he knew he still loved her and now, waiting for her, wondering if she will come back to him or if she’s already in a relationship with another man.

songs.full_title: Don't Come Easy by Isaiah Firebrace
songs.title: Don’t Come Easy

description.plain:
“Don’t Come Easy” by Isaiah represented Australia at the 2017 Eurovision Song Contest held in Kyiv, Ukraine. The song placed 6th in the semi-final, and placed 9th in the Grand Final with 173 points.

Isaiah was internally selected by Australian broadcaster SBS on March 7, 2017 along with the song. Isaiah was announced as the Australian entry during a special event held in Melbourne, Australia, where he performed the 2017 entry along with his previous singles.
